What you need to know:  South Africa Rugby tournament director Yusuf Jackson disclosed Tuesday that Kenya Simbas, who are currently in South Africa will play two of their Currie Cup matches in Nairobi in June this yearJackson said it's South Africa's wish to create Rugby opportunities for players not only in South Africa but across the continentJackson said that this is a great moment to strengthen Africa rugby since it will expose players as well as give them a feel and taste of continent